The paper discusses optical machine learning methods for image recognition, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses improvements to the training process and the integration of optical and electronic neural networks, which are topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of diffractive optical networks also has applications in robotics (cs.RO) and neural engineering (cs.NE).
